HEADWORD: Tobacconist
<hw>To*bac"co*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
dealer in tobacco; also, a manufacturer of tobacco.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A smoker of tobacco.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sylvester.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>To-beat</ent>⟦br⟧
